<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="829" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d829">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">857.014/60</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    War</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-05">February 5, 1929</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: With reference to your
                            letter of January 28, 1929, in which you state that the Island of Bouvet
                            in the South Atlantic was placed under the sovereignty of Norway by the
                            Royal Decree of January 23, 1928, I am pleased to advise you that the
                            War Department knows of no American interest that would be jeopardized
                            by a recognition of Norway’s action in this case.<note n="11a" xml:id="d829fn11a">A reply to the same effect was received from the
                                Navy Department on February 1.</note></p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed>C. B. <hi rend="smallcaps">Robbins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>